{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"17ed3f71-2ccd-438f-abcd-1c92a957d00d","content":"Yes, you'll run into **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for older TFMs. Looking at your targets:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET (Core) side. You'll need to update those two targets (e.g., to `net6.0` / `net8.0`).\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n\n1. **Package consolidation** — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n2. **Breaking API changes** — some deprecated APIs were removed; review the [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) after updating your TFMs.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6661c560-98f1-4e5e-864c-c5f1235a03b0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. The user wants to migrate to MSTest v3. Let me think about compatibility issues:\n\n1. **MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks.** MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+. Let me be more precise:\n   - MSTest v3 (MSTest.TestFramework 3.x) dropped support for:\n     - `netcoreapp3.1` — this is out of support and MSTest v3 no longer targets it\n     - `net5.0` — also out of support and not targeted by MSTest v3\n   - `net462` should still be supported by MSTest v3\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: MSTest v3 introduced the `MSTest` meta-package (instead of separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages).\n\n3. **Breaking changes in MSTest v3**: Some APIs were removed or changed, assertions may behave differently, etc.\n\nSo the key compatibility issues are that `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` won't work with MSTest v3 and need to be removed or updated to supported frameworks, while `net462` can stay as-is.","outputTokens":622,"requestId":"0422:1C1C65:22F15CD:278A147:69E831B5"},"id":"2fb960e6-5a50-42ba-9e27-be4af50794a4","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:26:09.317Z","parentId":"98fc564b-9bcb-420e-ac24-a0d3ff384150"}
